Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSelectedWireState(25.10)                        setSelectedWireState(25.10)

Name
       setSelectedWireState - Sets the state of the selected wire

Syntax
       setSelectedWireState

       [-help]

       <index>

       <value>

       Sets the state of the selected wire.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setSelectedWireState parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setSelectedWireState

       <index>
              Specifies which selected wire shape needs to be set.

       <value>
              Specifies  the  state  to  be set for the selected wire. You can
              specify one of the following values:

              * ROUTED

              * FIXED

              * COVER

              * NOSHIELD

              * UNKNOWN

Related Information
              * The wire section in the Innovus  Database  Object  Information
                manual

              * Editing Wires chapter of the User Guide

